<subSubSection id="4170B973E653C582805FF287F5CA7027" pageId="20" pageNumber="39" type="notes">
<paragraph id="48644BDDAC128C87C7754D8E5D28DCBF" pageId="20" pageNumber="39">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3578BAA52BE3BCE3F822FC25C3AE3C8" pageId="20" pageNumber="39">
This species was removed from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="1BC0697B48034D3C5C337C918ED81367" genus="X." lsidName="X. bispinatus" pageId="20" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="bispinatus">X. bispinatus</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="2EFB9A53F02C3633E593803B39D41D4F" author="Kirkendall, LR" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="31" pageNumber="50" pagination="729 - 743" title="The bark and ambrosia beetles (Curculionidae, Scolytinae) of Cocos Island, Costa Rica and the role of mating systems in island zoogeography." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8312.2006.00698.x" volume="89" year="2006">Kirkendall and Jordal (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="5FA509D371907E19024B58BC712CAD6A" genus="X." lsidName="X. bispinatus" pageId="20" pageNumber="39" rank="species" species="bispinatus">X. bispinatus</taxonomicName>
by the smaller size, discal interstrial setae sparse or absent, and by its light orange to reddish brown color (
<bibRefCitation id="B562705845BA89E6B4B768680AC2C2F2" author="Atkinson, TH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="30" pageNumber="49" pagination="96 - 100" title="Occurrence of Xyleborusbispinatus (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae) Eichhoff in southern Florida." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3669.1.10" volume="3669" year="2013">Atkinson et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
